    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nohup\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Nohup</a> will detach a process you run from your current console and let it continue when you close the terminal.  Run something like this. </p>\n\n<pre><code>nohup java -jar my.jar &amp;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>By default it will pipe the output to nohup.out, so if you don't want that you could try:</p>\n\n<pre><code>nohup java -jar my.jar &gt; /dev/null &amp;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
